#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn45.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Avijjāvagga "
msgstr "1. Ignorance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Jāṇussoṇibrāhmaṇasutta → brāhmaṇasuttaṃ (bj) | brāhmaṇo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Jāṇussoṇibrāhmaṇasutta "
msgstr "4. Regarding the Brahmin Jāṇussoṇi "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

#. VAR: vaḷavābhirathena → vaḷabhīrathena (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā ānando jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ. "
msgstr "He saw the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi driving out of Sāvatthī in a splendid all-white chariot drawn by mares. "

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.4"
msgid "Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati. "
msgstr "The yoked horses were pure white, as were the ornaments, chariot, upholstery, reins, goad, and canopy. And his turban, robes, sandals were white, as was the chowry fanning him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr "When people saw it they exclaimed, "

# NOTE: I keep the overly literal Brahma here to retain consistency with the similar usage at AN 3.63. I found that only by keeping the literal form was the sense retained. But I might change my mind!
msgctxt "sn45.4:1.6"
msgid "“brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Wow! That’s a Brahmā vehicle! "

msgctxt "sn45.4:1.7"
msgid "Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho”ti. "
msgstr "It’s a vehicle fit for Brahmā!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.5, sc2
msgctxt "sn45.4:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened, adding, "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn45.4:3.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.2"
msgid "Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāyantaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.3"
msgid "Setā sudaṃ assā yuttā honti setālaṅkārā, seto ratho, setaparivāro, setā rasmiyo, setā patodalaṭṭhi, setaṃ chattaṃ, setaṃ uṇhīsaṃ, setāni vatthāni, setā upāhanā, setāya sudaṃ vālabījaniyā bījīyati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.5"
msgid "‘brahmaṃ vata, bho, yānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.6"
msgid "Brahmayānarūpaṃ vata, bho’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn45.4:3.7"
msgid "Sakkā nu kho, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmayānaṃ paññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, can you point out a Brahmā vehicle in this teaching and training?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn45.4:4.1"
msgid "“Sakkā, ānandā”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“I can, Ānanda,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:4.2"
msgid "“imasseva kho etaṃ, ānanda, ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ: "
msgstr "“These are all terms for the noble eightfold path: "

msgctxt "sn45.4:4.3"
msgid "‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipīti. "
msgstr "‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in battle’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.6, sc5
msgctxt "sn45.4:5.1"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhi, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosavinayapariyosānā hoti, mohavinayapariyosānā hoti. "
msgstr "When right view is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal of greed, hate, and delusion. "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.2"
msgid "Sammāsaṅkappo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosavinayapariyosāno hoti, mohavinayapariyosāno hoti. "
msgstr "When right thought … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.3"
msgid "Sammāvācā, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosānā hoti. "
msgstr "right speech … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.4"
msgid "Sammākammanto, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti. "
msgstr "right action … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.5"
msgid "Sammāājīvo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti. "
msgstr "right livelihood … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.6"
msgid "Sammāvāyāmo, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti. "
msgstr "right effort … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.7"
msgid "Sammāsati, ānanda, bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosānā hoti. "
msgstr "right mindfulness … "

msgctxt "sn45.4:5.8"
msgid "Sammāsamādhi, ānanda, bhāvito bahulīkato rāgavinayapariyosāno hoti, dosa … pe … mohavinayapariyosāno hoti. "
msgstr "right immersion is developed and cultivated it culminates with the removal of greed, hate, and delusion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn45.4:6.1"
msgid "Iminā kho etaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā imassevetaṃ ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ: "
msgstr "This is a way to understand how these are all terms for the noble eightfold path: "

msgctxt "sn45.4:6.2"
msgid "‘brahmayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘dhammayānaṃ’ itipi, ‘anuttaro saṅgāmavijayo’ itipī”ti. "
msgstr "‘vehicle of Brahmā’, or else ‘vehicle of truth’, or else ‘supreme victory in battle’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.4:6.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn45.4:7.1"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.1"
msgid "“Yassa saddhā ca paññā ca, "
msgstr "“Its qualities of faith and wisdom "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sadā dhuraṃ → saddhā dhuraṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.2"
msgid "Dhammā yuttā sadā dhuraṃ; "
msgstr "are always yoked to the shaft. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.3"
msgid "Hirī īsā mano yottaṃ, "
msgstr "Conscience is its pole, mind its strap, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:8.4"
msgid "Sati ārakkhasārathi. "
msgstr "and mindfulness its careful driver. "

# NOTE: BB has “adornment” here, but parikkhara is always, so far as I know, used in the sense of something essential, as indeed is sila.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.1"
msgid "Ratho sīlaparikkhāro, "
msgstr "The chariot’s equipped with ethics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.2"
msgid "jhānakkho cakkavīriyo; "
msgstr "its axle is absorption, and energy its wheel. "

# NOTE: The Chinese parallel at SA 769 is exact and helpful: 捨三昧為轅. see https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/dhurasamadhi-in-sn-45-4/4157/2
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Upekkhā → upekhā (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.3"
msgid "Upekkhā dhurasamādhi, "
msgstr "Equanimity and immersion are the carriage-shaft, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:9.4"
msgid "anicchā parivāraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "and it’s upholstered with desirelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: Abyāpādo → avyāpādo (bj)
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.1"
msgid "Abyāpādo avihiṃsā, "
msgstr "Good will, harmlessness, and seclusion "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.2"
msgid "viveko yassa āvudhaṃ; "
msgstr "are its weapons, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: cammasannāho → vammasannāho (bj) | dhammasannāho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.3"
msgid "Titikkhā cammasannāho, "
msgstr "patience its shield and armor, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:10.4"
msgid "yogakkhemāya vattati. "
msgstr "as it rolls on to sanctuary. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.1"
msgid "Etadattani sambhūtaṃ, "
msgstr "This supreme Brahmā vehicle "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.2"
msgid "brahmayānaṃ anuttaraṃ; "
msgstr "arises in oneself. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.3"
msgid "Niyyanti dhīrā lokamhā, "
msgstr "The wise leave the world in it, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.4"
msgid "aññadatthu jayaṃ jayan”ti. "
msgstr "sure of winning the victory.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.4:11.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
